headline: Why I Just Bought More of These 2 High-Yield Dividend Stocks in My Retirement Account and Expect to Continue Loading Up on Their Shares in 2025
summary: The thesis is simple: Dividend stocks have historically outperformed non-payers by a wide margin.  According to data from Ned Davis Research and Hartford Funds, dividend growers have delivered a 10.2% average annual total return over the last 50 years, compared to 4.3% for the average non-dividend payer.  Camden Property Trust (NYSE: CPT) and EastGroup Properties (NYSE: EGP) certainly fit the bill.
